Html: When I try to put transfrm.8xk in the Archive of Wabbit I get an error message that there is "Not enough free space on the calculator." The app is 31k in size.

Usually this is associated with a bad or corrupted file. Where did you get the file from? It's also possible that you don't have enough archive space left. I'm assuming you check the free archive left (2nd + "+" + 2)?

You are right. I downloaded the file again and now it works. Thanks.
